				<p><p>The 3-axis gimbal stabilization system internally combines a 3-axis gyroscope and 3-axis accelerometer. It outputs PWM signals necessary for maintaining an orientation.  The outputs are typically meant to drive RC servos.</p>

<p>This <em>might</em> be enough for your use-case, but it is dependent on the details. </p>

<p>But generally, a gimbal stabilization system is not the same as accelerometer. An accelerometer operates at a lower level and provides x/y/z acceleration components at the measured instant in time only.  This gimbal system is outputting the corrections that would be needed to hold an orientation.  You might be able to derive acceleration from that to some extent, but that is not what it is intended for.</p>
